<br>
A bit of history on myself. I have played EQ since almost the start and the Pinene toon is over 6 years old now. I have seen everything and I feel I know just about all there is aboot the bard class.<br>
<br>
1. Instruments<br>
We need a reason to use them more often. IMHO bards should be using instruments 90% of the time. To do that an instrument needs to be more then just a raw mod. Maybe they should do more then just add a 3.4 mod to a song. Examples of what an instrument could add to a song are; an extra tick to song duration, increased song casting speed, reduced resist rates or increased range.  Give me a reason to use a horns, lutes, and flutes <br>
<br>
2. Song ideas<br>
As mentioned for 60 levels songs were extremely diverse and reflected the idea &quot;jack of all trades master of none&quot;. However, the last 3 years have showed a series of songs that reflect &quot;master of DS, over haste/nuke and resists and jack shit of anything else&quot;. We have lines of old songs that can be looked into for upgrades; the Nivs line and the Largos Line.<br>
<br>
3. Fleet of Foot<br>
Really by now it should affect the entire group like it says<br>
<br>
4. AE dot songs and the nerf<br>
I fully understand the need to address this issue. Due to wide spread use and asshole bards just hogging entire zones causing grief for other soloers and groups. I don’t blame anyone but us for the way AE dots work now. However, it’s broken a few things on how AE songs work. Two prime examples are; if a mob is fleeing due to being low life then no damage is done, Song of Midnight is described as &quot;Decrease Hit points by 8 (L56) to 9 (L70) per tick&quot; on Lucy. Now I know this song probably isn’t used all that much but a part of it is broken I don’t like broken. A couple &quot;IF&quot; statements in the code should be able to resolve both issues.<br>
<br>
5. Song Lands/Fades<br>
This was talked aboot at the last FF and I really hope it's looked in to finally.<br>
<br>
6. Fun<br>
I think I can say that most bards really don’t want more &quot;power per say&quot; (some extra melee output would be nice), but what we want is fun, fun songs, fun clickies, fun illusions, fun instruments. I log on to my bard cause I want to have fun not to play the same 3 or 4 song for 5 hours.<br>
<br>
7. Instrument Cap<br>
It was said this would be raised to something that wouldn't hinder increased mod effects but has yet to happen. It would be a start to item number 1.<br>
<br>
8. Defensive ability<br>
It is fairly easy to say bards are as much of a pulling class as a monk. Due to this roll we are more often then not the recipient of the Rampage effects of raid mobs. Even when not pulling area effect songs put us very high on the rampage list as its built. Now a simple FM will make you all safe and drop you to the bottom of the Rampage list but this could mean a cleric might be next on the list and a few seconds later is dead. Shield of Notes has helped a lot. But I feel deftdance could use a lower recycle time or some more benefit from our plate armor would also be appropriate.<br>
<br>
9. Puretone<br>
Puretone itself should be allowed to be used at a lower level. It is not as useful as it once was at level 60. A new disc should be introduced to allow for some increased functionality. One idea i like the most is make Puretone (or any upgrade disc) not only make all songs play at a minimal mod but also increase the mod a song is being played at by .5. An example; you are holding your drum that does 3.0 mod to your chant and use Puretone instead of doing nothing it would increase your over all mod for the chant to 3.5 as well supplying a 2.5 mod to all other songs you might be playing. In the case of a newer Puretone disc the base mod would be higher and the &quot;bonus&quot; mod would be greater too.  This, again, would be a start to helping item 1.<br>
<br>
10. Bard Melee<br>
If a bard chooses to use melee weapons over an instrument then the damage out put should reflect the loss in power of the songs. Most high end bards are averaging around 200dps and this, in comparison to most other classes, is pretty low at that stage in the game.<br>
