lass=title> Re: Pinene's Top 10 bard issues list</span><hr size=1> I don't care if you don't desire feedback, here is some anyway ;-p<br>
<br>
1. I completely agree that the role of the instrument-weilding bard has all but disappeared from EQ today.  I think that if we ever want to see anything like that happen tho, we're going to have to limit our suggestions to things that are relatively easy to code.  I think duration and song haste are<br>
pretty much out of the question for the standard 3 tick songs.  We could possibly get them to extend the duration of songs that already last longer than 3 ticks, since there must already be a line of code or two devoted to it.<br>
<br>
There's gonna be a lot of issues tho because I don't think there currently is any distinction in the code between a worn instrument mod, and a truely weilded instrument.  It is kind of ironic that by embracing the worn instrument mod on items, bards are now feeling the other edge of the blade by having the options of the true instrument weilder severely limited.<br>
<br>
There is always the possibility of adding an extra flag to true instruments and then add components to song with true instruments as regeants.  For example, a song could<br>
grant the regular hasteV1/str/atk/DS if sung with no instrument; a mod'ed version of those stats with a worn instrument mod; but if sung with a true instrument, would<br>
add 5 to accuracy, mod'ed to a possibly 20 accuracy depending on the power of the instrument.  Unfortunately, that requires work, and attention to a class no one plays.<br>
<br>
2.  It's so sad how most of us can probably just look at the song list from lvl 1 to 60, and come up with a whole new line up of songs for bards for the next expansion that will be a million times better than what we'll get.  In 15 minutes at that.<br>
<br>
3.  I don't think I would want that as top 10.  Makes it seem like we have nothing to complain about and we're reaching.  It's a coding bug and they won't fix it.<br>
<br>
4.  The devs are so happy they killed AE kiting that I'm sure they will not consider ever looking at that code again.  And they'll smile while they say no.  It did take them 3 tries afterall, that's a lot of work!<br>
<br>
5.  Same as number 3.<br>
<br>
6.  A lot of classes would say &quot;I would settle for 4 different spells to cast, i'm stuck with 2&quot;.  It's too similar to point #2 and &quot;fun&quot; probably means different things to different people.  RandomDev_01 says &quot;Royal Rumbles are teh funnest GM events ever!&quot;.  I think emphasising song variety is more important.  Let's get the devs to focus on songs lvl 1-60 and not 61-65 when they want to upgrade stuff.  Especially since the next expansion will not raise levels.<br>
<br>
7.  Unfortunately the raising of the instrument mod cap was part of the &quot;re-envisioning&quot;, and that's all over and done with.  Sony already moved the P.R. and marketing towards the next expansion so they won't respond to anything that was talked about in the re-envisioning anymore.  Sorry.<br>
<br>
8.  I liked how monks got their AC un-nerfed, got dodge-from-behind, and other things to help with pulling.<br>
A bard is a puller.  I like how wars,sk's, and pallies got a<br>
boost in AC because they were plate class.  A bard is a plate class.  WTF?  The more I look at it the more I think Sony works like a merrit guild (no offense to the 1% of the merrit guilds out there that actually work).<br>
<br>
9.  We might get puretone 2.0 at some point.  Probably the day after it becomes useless for some reason or another.<br>
<br>
10.  The problem with bard melee dps is that when the devs look at potential dps of classes when they are balancing them, they really go for the god-mode scenario.  This means a bard with max atk and all buffs, with another bard in the group singing battle songs, while playing dot songs and clicking in drums for max mod damage.  They can't separate melee dps from overall dps, from a balance perspective.  It's a raw deal for our pitiful melee dps, but in the overall dps department, we're kinda flying under the radar at the moment and in my opinion should not attempt to bring attention to it.<br>
<br>
Those are my thoughts,<br>
I like feedback, goes well with coffee in the morning.<br>
<br>
